<p style="margin-bottom:16px;"><strong>A real estate company in India is a Private Limited or LLP incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013 (or LLP Act, 2008) with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs, and registered as a promoter under Section 4 of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 with the relevant State Real Estate Regulatory Authority before launching any project.</strong></p>
