                <p>A real estate company in India is a Private Limited or LLP incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013 (or LLP Act, 2008) with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs, and registered as a promoter under Section 4 of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 with the relevant State Real Estate Regulatory Authority before launching any project. HARERA Gurugram registration is mandatory for any project where the plot area exceeds 500 square metres or more than 8 apartments are proposed for sale, per Section 3(2) RERA read with Rule 3 of the Haryana Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017.</p>
                <p>A real estate company is not one registration but two stacked compliance gates. The first is incorporation with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs - typically a Private Limited Company under the Companies Act, 2013 via SPICe+. The second is the promoter registration under Section 4 of the RERA Act, 2016 with the Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority, Gurugram. In Gurugram - which holds the densest concentration of HARERA-registered group housing in North India (DLF, M3M, Experion, Smart World) - this stack is what separates a sellable brochure from a Section 59 penalty notice. Patron Accounting LLP (15+ years and 10,000+ clients) runs the full chain from our Sector 48 office. Starting INR 14,999 (Exl GST and Govt. Charges).</p>
                <p>Content is reviewed quarterly for accuracy.</p>
