<!-- SECTION 3: WHAT IS GSTAT APPEAL FILING -->
<section class="content-section" id="what-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="column-content">
                <h2 class="section-title">What Is a Real Estate Company Registration in India</h2>
                <div class="content-text what-is-definition">
                    
                    
<p><strong>Real estate company registration is the two-step process of incorporating a Private Limited Company or LLP under the Companies Act 2013 with the Ministry of Corporate Affairs, and registering as a promoter under Section 4 of the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act 2016 with the State Real Estate Regulatory Authority.</strong></p>
<p>A real estate company can lawfully own land, enter into joint development agreements, accept booking amounts, and sell flats or plots only after both gates are cleared. HARERA Gurugram registration is mandatory for any project where the plot area exceeds 500 square metres or where more than eight apartments are proposed for sale, per Section 3(2) read with Rule 3 of the Haryana Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017.</p>
<p>The regulatory architecture spans four statutes. The <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Companies Act, 2013</a> (Sections 7 to 12 incorporation, registered office; Sections 137 and 92 annual filings via Form AOC-4 within 30 days of AGM and Form MGT-7 within 60 days) and the LLP Act 2008 set the entity vehicle. The RERA Act, 2016 (Section 4 application via Form A; Section 5 30-day decision plus deemed registration; Section 11 advertising and display requirements; Section 18 refund liability; Section 59 penalty up to 10 percent of project cost plus imprisonment up to 3 years; Section 2(zk) promoter definition; Section 2(zn) real estate project definition) sets the promoter registration framework. The <a href="https://haryanarera.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Haryana Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017</a> (Rule 3 registration; Rule 4 quarterly progress reports) plus the HARERA Gurugram Standard Fees Regulations, 2021 (INR 10 per sq.m. residential, INR 20 per sq.m. commercial, capped INR 5 lakh, INR 5 per sq.m. per day late fee) set the Gurugram-specific operational layer. The <a href="https://www.incometax.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Income-tax Act</a> (Section 80-IBA affordable housing deduction; Section 194-IA TDS on property sale above INR 50 lakh; Section 115BAA 22 percent concessional rate giving effective 25.17 percent) sets the direct tax position. The CGST Act, 2017 read with Notification 03/2019-CT(Rate) sets the 1 percent affordable housing and 5 percent other under-construction residential rates (no ITC), with commercial leasing at 18 percent.</p>
<p>The DTCP (Director of Town and Country Planning, Haryana) licence under the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975 read with the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Rules, 1976 is a precondition before HARERA application for most Gurugram colony projects. Pricing is on carpet area only (Section 2(k) RERA read with HARERA Gurugram ruling of 27 April 2022 - super-area pricing is treated as fraudulent). EDC (External Development Charges) and IDC (Internal Development Charges) payable to HSVP and the licensing authority are separate from the carpet-area-based basic sale price. The 70 percent escrow under Section 4(2)(l)(D) RERA mandates 70 percent of buyer collections to a dedicated project escrow account with quarterly CA certification.</p>
<p>Patron's role spans the full real estate stack - structure selection (Pvt Ltd, LLP, Section 8) and name approval with DTCP or HUDA name clearance for promoter-suggesting words, SPICe+ Part A and Part B filing with real-estate-tailored MoA object clauses (development, construction, sale, leasing, JV, fund management, REIT participation), DIN under Section 153 and DSC for directors, PAN, TAN, GSTIN under Haryana, Profession Tax, DTCP licence coordination, HARERA Gurugram Form A under Section 4 RERA with full attachment pack, 70 percent escrow account architecture, post-incorporation rolling compliance calendar (Form AOC-4, Form MGT-7, HARERA quarterly Rule 4 progress reports, annual audited statement, Section 80-IBA tracking, Section 194-IA TDS via Form 26QB, GST returns). Starting INR 14,999 (Exl GST and Govt. Charges).</p>


                </div>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <p><strong>Key Terms for Real Estate Company Registration:</strong></p>
                    
<div class="key-term"><strong>Promoter:</strong> Any individual or entity that constructs or causes to be constructed a real estate project for sale, including landowners participating in revenue or area sharing - defined under Section 2(zk) RERA Act, 2016.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Real Estate Project:</strong> Development of a building or plot for sale, including phasing, defined under Section 2(zn) RERA Act, 2016. Each phase is a separate registration.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Carpet Area:</strong> Net usable floor area excluding external walls, balcony, and verandah - the only legal basis for pricing real estate units, per Section 2(k) RERA and the HARERA Gurugram ruling of 27 April 2022.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>DTCP Licence:</strong> Licence granted by the Director of Town and Country Planning, Haryana under the Haryana Development and Regulation of Urban Areas Act, 1975 - a precondition before HARERA application for most Gurugram colony projects.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>EDC and IDC:</strong> External and Internal Development Charges payable to HSVP and the licensing authority - separate from carpet-area basic sale price under HARERA Gurugram model agreement.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 3 RERA Threshold:</strong> Project registration with HARERA is mandatory above 500 square metres plot area OR more than 8 apartments for sale; whichever first breached triggers registration.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 4 RERA Form A:</strong> Application format for HARERA project registration; covers DTCP licence, ownership, plans, brochure, financials, escrow declarations.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 5 RERA 30-day Decision:</strong> HARERA must grant or refuse registration within 30 days under Section 5(1); deemed registration applies under Section 5(2) if no decision.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 11 RERA Display:</strong> HARERA registration number, project page URL, and carpet-area-based price must appear on every advertisement, brochure, and website.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 59 RERA Penalty:</strong> Up to 10 percent of estimated project cost under Section 59(1); imprisonment up to 3 years under Section 59(2) for continued non-compliance.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 18 RERA Refund:</strong> Promoter liable to refund all collections to allottees with interest on delay or non-completion.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 4(2)(l)(D) Escrow:</strong> 70 percent of buyer collections mandated to a dedicated project escrow account with quarterly CA certification.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>HARERA Gurugram Standard Fees Regulations 2021:</strong> INR 10 per sq.m. residential, INR 20 per sq.m. commercial, capped at INR 5 lakh per project; late fee INR 5 per sq.m. per day capped at the registration fee.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>HARERA Gurugram vs Panchkula:</strong> HARERA Gurugram covers the entire Gurugram district under Notification 1/92/2017-1TCP dated 14 December 2017; HARERA Panchkula covers the rest of Haryana including Faridabad, Sonipat, Karnal and Panchkula district.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>SPICe+ Part A and B:</strong> Single integrated MCA web form for company incorporation - name reservation (Part A) plus incorporation with linked AGILE-PRO, e-MoA, e-AoA, INC-9 (Part B); returns CoI, CIN, PAN, TAN, EPFO, ESIC, Profession Tax in one cycle.</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 115BAA:</strong> Optional 22 percent concessional corporate tax rate under Income-tax Act; effective approx. 25.17 percent including surcharge and cess; once-and-for-all election via Form 10-IC; cannot claim Section 10AA, Section 32 additional depreciation, or specified Chapter VI-A deductions (other than Section 80JJAA and Section 80M).</div>
<div class="key-term"><strong>Section 80-IBA:</strong> Income-tax deduction for affordable housing projects subject to size, locality, completion timeline conditions; modelled against Section 115BAA before electing.</div>


                </div>
            </div>
