            <h2 class="section-title">Three Binding Clocks for Real Estate Company Compliance</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                Three binding clocks anchor every Gurugram real estate engagement. HARERA must decide within 30 days under Section 5(1) RERA - if Form A is filed incomplete, the clock resets and you lose at least 30 days of sales. MCA Form AOC-4 must be filed within 30 days of AGM under Section 137 Companies Act 2013, with a daily continuing fine up to INR 2,00,000 under Section 137(3). Section 194-IA TDS on property sale above INR 50 lakh must be deposited via Form 26QB within 30 days of the month of deduction - missed deposits attract interest under Section 201(1A). Beyond these, HARERA quarterly progress reports under Rule 4 Haryana RERA Rules 2017 and annual audited statement under Section 4(2)(l)(D) RERA must hit HARERA Gurugram on schedule. Pricing on super area instead of carpet area is treated as fraudulent per HARERA Gurugram ruling of 27 April 2022; 70 percent escrow leakage under Section 4(2)(l)(D) triggers HARERA enforcement; Section 11 RERA mandates HARERA registration number on every advertisement, brochure and website.

